{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7104c9",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"I:"
]
},
" “Mr. ___ is the sickest patient on our team and will need watching.”"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"723d1e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"P:"
]
},
" “He is a 57-year-old man with DM and cellulitis of the right leg. He was admitted with hypotension, fever, and concerns for fasciitis. He has stabilized after 2 liters of NS and vancomycin and piperacillin/tazobactam, but continues to have fevers and BPs in the 90s/50s. Leg CT is pending.”"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d7d975",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"A:"
]
},
" “Vancomycin level needs to be followed up at 8 ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"PM"
]
},
" and vital signs and volume status evaluated every 2 hours.”"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ce7d08",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"S:"
]
},
" “If SBP <80 mm Hg and there's no volume overload, give 500 mL NS IV bolus. If vancomycin level is <15, discuss with pharmacy dose changes. Follow up on leg CT.”"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2b7283",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"S:"
]
},
" “Okay, so Mr. ___ has severe cellulitis with hypotension and is on broad-spectrum antibiotics. He will need vital signs and volume exam every 2 hours and may require vancomycin dose adjustment and additional BP support with fluids. Follow-up on leg CT.”"
]
},
" "
]
}
